</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1773,2016]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Female. Body length 3.4 mm; wing length 3.7 mm. Frons and face wider than anterior ocellus width and wider than in male. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[378,458,1809,1833]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="8.[151,264,816,839]" captionTargetBox="[260,1324,344,788]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[260,1327,339,791]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. paratype female from Goiás, Brazil; 39, wing; 40, tergite 8, 10 and cercus (cercus broken), dorsal view; 41, sternite 8, lateral view; 42, sternite 8, 10 and cercus (cercus broken), ventral view; 43, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 40 – 42 = 0.2 mm; 43 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281638/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number box="[429,458,1809,1833]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
) with cell r 
<number box="[586,594,1824,1838]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
and base of cell r 
<number box="[789,797,1824,1838]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[806,813,1824,1838]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="3.0">3</number>
brown infuscated. Fore tarsi unicolorous. Tergite 
<number box="[1364,1378,1809,1833]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="8.[151,264,816,839]" captionTargetBox="[260,1324,344,788]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[260,1327,339,791]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Macrostomus nitidus, sp. nov. paratype female from Goiás, Brazil; 39, wing; 40, tergite 8, 10 and cercus (cercus broken), dorsal view; 41, sternite 8, lateral view; 42, sternite 8, 10 and cercus (cercus broken), ventral view; 43, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 40 – 42 = 0.2 mm; 43 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281638/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,180,1847,1871]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="40.0">40</number>
</figureCitation>
) with median and basal heavily sclerotized area. Sternite 
<number box="[804,818,1847,1871]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="8.0">8</number>
(
